-- A.J. Burnett to Be Examined After Bunt Hits Him in Eye, MLB.com Reports
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-03-01T05:02:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/a-j-burnett-to-be-examined-after-bunt-hits-him-in-eye-mlb-com-reports.html
Pittsburgh Pirates pitcher  A.J. Burnett  will have another examination of his right eye, which
was injured when he fouled a bunt back into his face,  MLB.com
reported .  Burnett will undergo tests today in Pittsburgh, General
Manager Neal Huntington told MLB.com.  Burnett, 35, had to leave a bunt-batting tournament in
spring training when he undercut the ball off a pitching
machine, causing it to ricochet off his face, the website said.  He was acquired by the Pirates from the  New York Yankees  on
Feb. 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
